I should note that according to http://www.hebcal.com/ the first candle sho=
uld
be lit at Saturday's nightfall (between the Sat and Sunday daytimes). What
makes it more confusing is that in the Jewish tradition, the day starts at
nightfall and extends to the night and the day time (Possibly due to Genesi=
s I
- =E2=80=9CAnd God called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night, =
and there
was evening and there was morning, the first day.=E2=80=9D (and so on for t=
he other
days).

